snippet: At least five lawmakers from the party of President Mikheil Saakashvili were reported injured after an angry crowd of protesters attacked in Tbilisi.
abstract: Angry crowd attacks allies of Georgia's Pres Mikheil Saakashvili outside site for annual address to nation, as Georgia’s five-month-old power-sharing experiment deteriorates into open conflict; at least five lawmakers from president’s party are reported injured.

byline.original: By OLESYA VARTANYAN and ELLEN BARRY
byline.contributor: Olesya Vartanyan reported from Tbilisi, and Ellen Barry from Moscow.

lead_paragraph: At least five lawmakers from the party of President Mikheil Saakashvili were reported injured after an angry crowd of protesters attacked in Tbilisi.

headline.seo: In Georgia, Crowd Attacks Mikheil Saakashvili’s Allies
headline.main: Demonstrators Attack Allies of Georgian President, Injuring at Least 5
headline.print_headline: Demonstrators Attack Allies of Georgian President, Injuring at Least 5
